==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Herringbone
<hw>Her"ring*bone`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧r"r⟦icr⟧ng*b⟦omac⟧n`)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or like, the spine of a herring;
especially, characterized by an arrangement of work in rows of parallel
lines, which in the alternate rows slope in different
directions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Herringbone stitch</b></col>, <cd>a kind of cross-stitch
in needlework, chiefly used in flannel.</cd>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Herrnhuter</ent>⟦br⟧
